WEBVTT

00:00.418 --> 00:02.128
[Bosch]
Previously on Bosch: Legacy.

00:02.211 --> 00:03.045
Gun, gun, gun!

00:05.339 --> 00:08.175
So from your vantage point,
you did not see a gun?

00:08.259 --> 00:09.385
Correct.

00:09.468 --> 00:12.555
[Chandler] Rose and Associates
will be representing the Davis family

00:12.638 --> 00:14.932
in a wrongful death action
against the LAPD.

00:15.015 --> 00:16.517
Always looking for the pot of gold.

00:16.600 --> 00:17.435
[Chandler]
Can we meet?

00:17.518 --> 00:20.354
Talk about the audio recording
you had Mrs. Davis make.

00:20.438 --> 00:21.272
[Mrs. Davis on tape]
Does he still have his gun?

00:21.355 --> 00:23.482
[Nicole on tape]
Yes, it's in the trunk.

00:23.566 --> 00:25.860
[Mo] The good doctor's
most recent prescription audit.

00:25.943 --> 00:28.028
Who wrote the most opioid scripts?

00:28.112 --> 00:30.448
Dr. Vince Shipman by a mile.

00:30.531 --> 00:32.742
[Rendon] What if one of his doctors
was overprescribing?

00:32.825 --> 00:35.161
Writing scripts for nonexistent patients.

00:35.244 --> 00:37.663
I called Dr. Basu to follow up.
He didn't get back to me.

00:37.747 --> 00:39.498
Next thing I know, he's murdered.

00:39.582 --> 00:41.417
We're just canvassing the neighborhood.

00:41.500 --> 00:43.544
Uh, there's been a series
of daytime sexual assaults.

00:43.627 --> 00:44.462
You may have heard.

00:44.545 --> 00:45.379
No, I hadn't heard that.

00:45.463 --> 00:47.798
[Maddie]
Are you in the area often, mister...

00:47.882 --> 00:50.509
Dockweiler. Kurt Dockweiler.

00:50.593 --> 00:53.262
My client was the biological father
of Dominick Santanello.

00:53.345 --> 00:54.180
Your grandfather.

00:54.263 --> 00:56.015
You should know
his estate goes to his heirs.

00:56.098 --> 00:57.099
You and your son.

00:57.183 --> 01:00.269
If DNA confirms bloodlines,
which it will.

01:00.352 --> 01:01.312
We have a match.

01:01.395 --> 01:03.189
Now all we gotta do is keep 'em alive.

01:03.272 --> 01:04.315
I'm gonna post up on the heirs.

01:04.398 --> 01:06.942
I'll let Vibiana know
you're gonna be keeping an eye out.

01:07.026 --> 01:07.860
[camera shutter clicks]

01:09.028 --> 01:10.029
[Creighton]
Fucking traitor.

01:10.112 --> 01:11.655
I'll take care of it.

01:11.739 --> 01:14.158
Mr. Sloan just called to come up.
To do a security check.

01:14.241 --> 01:15.743
Okay, so he's probably just being--

01:15.826 --> 01:17.536
He did one tonight already, Harry.

01:17.620 --> 01:18.496
Okay, you need to get out of there.

01:18.579 --> 01:19.705
-What is it?
-Just come with me. It's okay.

01:19.789 --> 01:20.623
[Bosch] Take the stairs
and get out of there.

01:20.706 --> 01:22.208
I'm on my way. I'll find you.

01:24.627 --> 01:26.170
[tires screech]

01:29.507 --> 01:30.716
-Hurry!
-Okay!

01:33.219 --> 01:34.804
Go, quick!

01:36.180 --> 01:37.598
-[gasps]
-Quiet.

01:37.681 --> 01:38.974
[lock breaks]

01:43.103 --> 01:45.147
[suspenseful music playing]

01:49.151 --> 01:50.027
[gasps]

01:52.988 --> 01:55.699
[phone vibrates]

02:20.683 --> 02:22.643
Shh, shh, shh.

02:31.735 --> 02:34.738
[elevator whirring]

02:40.911 --> 02:41.912
[elevator stops]

02:52.089 --> 02:55.092
[elevator whirring]

04:17.925 --> 04:20.219
Let's go. Come on. Go. Come on.

04:23.555 --> 04:24.390
Go, go, go.

04:28.060 --> 04:29.269
[engine starts]

04:29.353 --> 04:30.729
Hang on.

04:38.195 --> 04:40.656
[tires screech]

04:43.075 --> 04:43.909
You all right?

04:43.993 --> 04:45.619
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

